        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">অনুবাদ:</span><span class=\"english\"> আন্দোলনের প্রভাব যে বাড়ছে</span><span class=\"english\">, </span><span class=\"english\">তার প্রমাণ মেলে ৭ই জুলাই</span><span class=\"english\">, </span><span class=\"english\">২০২৪-এ আয়োজিত </span><span class=\"english\">‘</span><span class=\"english\">বাংলা ব্লকেড</span><span class=\"english\">’</span><span class=\"english\"> কর্মসূচির মাধ্যমে। এটি ছিল দেশব্যাপী একটি সমন্বিত কর্মসূচি</span><span class=\"english\">, </span><span class=\"english\">যার আওতায় প্রধান প্রধান মহাসড়ক</span><span class=\"english\">, </span><span class=\"english\">সড়ক ও রেলপথ অবরোধ করা হয়। এই অবরোধের ফলে রাজধানী ঢাকাসহ দেশের গুরুত্বপূর্ণ অর্থনৈতিক ও প্রশাসনিক কেন্দ্রগুলো কার্যত অচল হয়ে পড়ে। এই কৌশলগত পদক্ষেপটি কেবল দেশের যোগাযোগ ব্যবস্থাকেই বিপর্যস্ত করেনি</span><span class=\"english\">, </span><span class=\"english\">বরং বিক্ষোভকারীদের সংগঠিত হওয়ার অসাধারণ ক্ষমতাকেও সবার সামনে তুলে ধরে। </span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">নম্বর বণ্টন:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">যথাযথভাবে অনুবাদ করার জন্য ০৫ নম্বর। কোনো লাইন মিস করলে ১.২৫ নম্বর কর্তন করা হবে।</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">বিশেষ দ্রষ্টব্য</span><span class=\"english\">: </span><span class=\"english\">লাইনগুলোর সঠিক ভাবানুবাদ লিখতে পারলে পূর্ণ নম্বর পাবে। আক্ষরিক অনুবাদ লেখার প্রয়োজন নেই</span><span class=\"english\">।</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">[</span><span class=\"english\">প্রতি ২টি বানান ভুলের জন্য ০১ নম্বর করে কর্তন করা হবে।</span><span class=\"english\">]</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">পরীক্ষক</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">ভুলগুলো</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">আন্ডারলাইন</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">করে</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">অবশ্যই</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">ঠিক</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">করে</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">দিবেন</span><span class=\"english\">।</span></p>"
    },
    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Write a paragraph on </span><span class=\"english\">“The Austere Love of Parents”</span><span class=\"english\"> within 10 sentences.                  </span><span class=\"english\">10</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">The Austere Love of Parents</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">The \"austere and lonely offices\" of a parent's love are often performed in silence, without expectation of gratitude or even notice. This form of devotion is not grand or flamboyant, but rather a constant, quiet presence felt in small, selfless acts. It is the love of a parent who rises in the pre-dawn darkness to prepare for the day. ​They do this to ensure the comfort and well-being of a family that remains asleep. This dedication is often born from hard work, endured for a child's future. What a child often fails to understand is that these sacrifices are the very foundation of their security and warmth. In their youthful self-absorption, they may not recognize the emotional or physical toll these acts take. It's a love that, by its very nature, can feel solitary to the person giving it, as the full weight of its meaning is not shared or acknowledged by those who benefit most. The true, poignant realization of this love often comes later in life, a moment of profound insight that makes us wish we could go back and simply say thank you. Ultimately, this journey from a child's ignorance to an adult's understanding reveals that the deepest form of love is often the most quietly given.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest Mark ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------09 Marks </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(A) For Title (</span><span class=\"english\">The Austere Love of Parents</span><span class=\"english\">) </span><span class=\"english\">-----------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Topic Sentence (Introduction)</span><span class=\"english\"> -------------------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Parental love often manifests in silence, without expectation of gratitude or notice, expressing a constant, selfless presence in small, selfless acts.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(C) Context Explanation (</span><span class=\"english\">Parental Love and Its Impact on Children</span><span class=\"english\">)</span><span class=\"english\"> -------------------------06 Marks                                                           </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">1. </span><span class=\"english\">Parents make silent sacrifices every day for their children’s comfort and future.                                                                               </span><span class=\"english\">2</span><span class=\"english\">. Their love is shown through actions, not words — such as waking up early to prepare for the day.                                     </span><span class=\"english\">3</span><span class=\"english\">. Children often don’t realize or appreciate the effort and hardship behind these acts.                                                                         </span><span class=\"english\">4</span><span class=\"english\">. The love of a parent can feel lonely because it is rarely fully understood or acknowledged.                                                               </span><span class=\"english\">5</span><span class=\"english\">. As people grow older, they come to recognize the depth of this love and feel grateful for it.                                                                                          </span><span class=\"english\">6</span><span class=\"english\">. The realization often brings a sense of regret for not expressing thanks sooner.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(D) Conclusion --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------01 Mark </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">The journey from childhood ignorance to adult understanding reveals that the deepest form of love is often the most quietly given.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">1. </span><span class=\"english\">For every 3 spelling/grammatical mistakes, 01 mark has to be deducted.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">2</span><span class=\"english\">. We will consider up to 12 sentences. However, if a student writes more than 12 sentences but less than double (20 sentences), 50% of the deserving marks must be deducted. If it becomes double (20 sentences), full marks have to be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">Comment: Write within 10 sentences.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">3. </span><span class=\"english\">Students must write within a para. If a student writes more than one para, half of the deserving marks must be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">(Comment: Write within single/one para)</span><span class=\"english\">.</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">4.</span><span class=\"english\"> For writing only the title of the paragraph bears no mark.</span></p>"
    },
    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">“Relationships are of different kinds.”</span><span class=\"english\"> Explain this statement with reference to the context.                     </span><span class=\"english\">5</span><span> </span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Relationships vary significantly in their nature and purpose. Some are familial and intimate, such as those with blood relatives or a spouse, providing deep emotional and psychological connections. Other relationships are social, like friendships, which are based on shared interests and mutual support. We also form relationships in educational settings with teachers and classmates, which can evolve from professional to personal bonds. Additionally, relationships can extend beyond human-to-human interaction to include bonds with animals or even inanimate objects, like a child's favorite toy, highlighting the diverse ways humans connect. Finally, relationships in the workplace may start as professional but often become social, showcasing how different contexts can shape the type of bond formed.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:                                                                              </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Mark</span><span class=\"english\">--------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">05 Marks</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(A) Identification of the Quote and Source </span><span class=\"english\">---------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span></p><p><span> </span><span class=\"english\">• </span><span class=\"english\">The given line has been taken from the lesson ‘Family Relationship’.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Context Explanation (</span><span class=\"english\">Understanding Relationships</span><span class=\"english\">) </span><span class=\"english\">(</span><span class=\"english\">Any</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">4 Points</span><span class=\"english\">) ---</span><span class=\"english\">04 Marks</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">• Familial and intimate relationships: Provide emotional and psychological connections.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Social relationships: Based on shared interests and mutual support.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Educational relationships: Can evolve from professional to personal bonds.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Beyond human-to-human interaction: Bonds with animals or inanimate objects.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Workplace relationships: Can start as professional but often become social.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">**For every 03 spelling or grammatical errors, 01 mark has to be deducted. However, mistakes regarding capital and small letters can be overlooked.</span><span> </span></p>"
    },
    {
        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Read the text below and fill in the gaps with the clues given in the box. There are more words than necessary. Make any grammatical changes (if necessary).</span><span class=\"english\"><span> </span>                   5</span></p><p><span><img src=\"images/Varsity_Kha_Weekly_Live_Exam-08_Set_3_3d6ee3ad.png\"/></span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Robert Hayden was born into a poor family in Detroit in USA in 1913 and had a difficult childhood beset (a)___eyesight problems. He was raised in part by (b)__ parents and missed a father's caring love. But in the (c)__, which is about a childhood memory, he writes about a father - probably his own-- who is harsh and often angry, (d)__does love his son in his own way. Hayden, a black American, wrote about black (e)____and history. He died in 1980.</span></p>",
